-- Poland plans to sell $470 mln stake in energy firm PGE
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Tue Jul 01, 2014 11:47AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, July 1 (Reuters) - The Polish state wants to sell around 65 million of its shares in energy firm PGE <PGE.WA>, with Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>, Goldman Sachs [GLDSH.UL] and Unicredit <CRDI.MI> to organise the transaction, Deutsche Bank said in a statement on Tuesday.

The sale is to take place via accelerated book-building. On the basis of Tuesday's closing price, the 3.47-percent stake in PGE would be worth 1.42 billion zlotys ($468.63 million).